utral", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": []}}, {"id": "2069967184302850213", "url": "https://x.com/aeberman12/status/2069967184302850213", "text": "Many analysts expect Hormuz to return to pre-war normal\n\n@TheStudyofWar argues the opposite \n\nIt's using the ceasefire to create permanent leverage\n\nThe probability of normalized flows is therefore almost zero \n\nBecause that would reduce Iran's leverage to almost zero\n\n#OOTT #Oil #Hormuz #Iran #Geop", "time": "02:13", "author": "aeberman12", "author_name": "Art Berman", "followers": 53616, "views": 7897, "likes": 55, "replies": 5, "retweets": 7, "quotes": 0, "bookmarks": 11, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bullish", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["Geopolitics", "Iran"]}}, {"id": "2069968057380802568", "url": "https://x.com/aeberman12/status/2069968057380802568", "text": "The IRGC Navy just rejected the Oman-IMO Hormuz transit plan\n\nAnalysts may think the Hormuz crisis is over\n\nIran disagrees.\n\nWithout an ongoing crisis or threat of crisis, Iran has no power except as a fee taker\n\n#OOTT #Oil #Hormuz #Iran #Shipping", "time": "02:16", "author": "aeberman12", "author_name": "Art Berman", "followers": 53616, "views": 6632, "likes": 54, "replies": 9, "retweets": 6, "quotes": 1, "bookmarks": 4, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bullish", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["Geopolitics", "Iran"]}}, {"id": "2069968888884760728", "url": "https://x.com/aeberman12/status/2069968888884760728", "text": "Watch the Hormuz inflows, not just the outflows.\n\nMore ships are leaving Hormuz\n\nFar fewer are returning\n\nThe traffic jam is clearing but cars are avoiding the freeway\n\nThat's not a return to normal—it's lingering caution\n\n#OOTT #Oil #Hormuz #Shipping #Energy", "time": "02:20", "author": "aeberman12", "author_name": "Art Berman", "followers": 53616, "views": 10011, "likes": 120, "replies": 6, "retweets": 25, "quotes": 2, "bookmarks": 8, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bullish", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["Tankers/shipping", "Supply outlook"]}}, {"id": "2069981725275430973", "url": "https://x.com/aeberman12/status/2069981725275430973", "text": "Rabobank's @TheMichaelEvery offers the best strategic view of the Iran crisis so far\n\nThis isn't peace—it's an armistice with multiple unresolved fault lines\n\nThat armistice could last quite a while IMO but Israel could blow it up\n#OOTT #Oil #Hormuz #Iran #Geopolitics https://t.co/UFbBdz0k2D", "time": "03:11", "author": "aeberman12", "author_name": "Art Berman", "followers": 53616, "views": 20418, "likes": 34, "replies": 1, "retweets": 2, "quotes": 1, "bookmarks": 9, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Neutral", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["Geopolitics", "Iran"]}}, {"id": "2069983679938527509", "url": "https://x.com/aeberman12/status/2069983679938527509", "text": "Scott Bessent may have revealed the administration's real theory, writes Molly Schwartz\n\n\"We didn't have regime change, but we changed the regime\"\n\nIf that's true, the Iran deal isn't surrender—it's a wager that coercion changed Tehran's behavior. \n\nWhat nonsense.\n\n #Iran #OOTT #Geopolitics #Oil #Tr", "time": "03:19", "author": "aeberman12", "author_name": "Art Berman", "followers": 53616, "views": 4241, "likes": 85, "replies": 9, "retweets": 6, "quotes": 1, "bookmarks": 2, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Neutral", "emotional_sentiment": "Negative", "topics": ["Geopolitics", "Iran"]}}, {"id": "2070032330828177813", "url": "https://x.com/JavierBlas/status/2070032330828177813", "text": "Brent crude is now a pre-war levels at around $72.5 a barrel. \n\nThe Brent futures market peaked on April 30th at $126.41 a barrel.", "time": "06:32", "author": "JavierBlas", "author_name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "views": 55453, "likes": 356, "replies": 18, "retweets": 67, "quotes": 4, "bookmarks": 9, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bearish", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["Prices/technicals"]}}, {"id": "2070033189028913546", "url": "https://x.com/JavierBlas/status/2070033189028913546", "text": "Oil-rich Venezuela was hit by one of the biggest earthquakes in its history (two consecutive tremors) on Wednesday evening, toppling buildings in Caracas. Early reports say oil production and exports appear unaffected. \n\n https://t.co/N4zx5ojg5P", "time": "06:35", "author": "JavierBlas", "author_name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "views": 26272, "likes": 120, "replies": 12, "retweets": 27, "quotes": 3, "bookmarks": 7, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Neutral", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["Venezuela"]}}, {"id": "2070064384353685685", "url": "https://x.com/cbjom/status/2070064384353685685", "text": "Next war in the Middle East will be an oil price war, not the other kind of war.\n\n#OOTT", "time": "08:39", "author": "cbjom", "author_name": "Crudehead🛢", "followers": 17544, "views": 21089, "likes": 73, "replies": 8, "retweets": 10, "quotes": 2, "bookmarks": 15, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Neutral", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["Geopolitics", "OPEC+"]}}, {"id": "2070065783330218370", "url": "https://x.com/JavierBlas/status/2070065783330218370", "text": "Iraq to OPEC: increase our oil production quota — or else!!!\n\nhttps://t.co/eLDsy0pM0d", "time": "08:45", "author": "JavierBlas", "author_name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "views": 32463, "likes": 206, "replies": 9, "retweets": 39, "quotes": 4, "bookmarks": 18, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bearish", "emotional_sentiment": "Negative", "topics": ["OPEC+"]}}, {"id": "2070087372440523051", "url": "https://x.com/LiveSquawk/status/2070087372440523051", "text": "#OOTT Three Oil Tankers Passing Through The Strait Of Hormuz Through The Southern Corridor Are Bypassing And Returning To The Persian @mizanplus\nhttps://t.co/ZVXDeC8Qiz", "time": "10:11", "author": "LiveSquawk", "author_name": "LiveSquawk", "followers": 436347, "views": 19679, "likes": 9, "replies": 2, "retweets": 3, "quotes": 0, "bookmarks": 1, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bullish", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["Tankers/shipping", "Geopolitics"]}}, {"id": "2070116566037913608", "url": "https://x.com/JavierBlas/status/2070116566037913608", "text": "Saudi Arabia appears to be about re-starting oil loadings inside the Persian Gulf. \n\nThree Saudi-owned in ballast VLCCs are concentrating around the Ju’aymah terminal (it has 6 single point moorings).\n\nIf the loadings go ahead, it would be the first known since early March.", "time": "12:07", "author": "JavierBlas", "author_name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "views": 208567, "likes": 386, "replies": 12, "retweets": 71, "quotes": 5, "bookmarks": 35, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bearish", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["Supply outlook", "Tankers/shipping"]}}, {"id": "2070123042504647054", "url": "https://x.com/JavierBlas/status/2070123042504647054", "text": "The three tankers crossed the Strait of Hormuz into the Persian Gulf over the last 48 hours with their location transponder off. Other Saudi owned VLCCs that were just outside the SoH appear to have gone “dark” too, indicating more potential inbound tankers.", "time": "12:32", "author": "JavierBlas", "author_name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "views": 14808, "likes": 49, "replies": 3, "retweets": 6, "quotes": 1, "bookmarks": 5, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bearish", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["Tankers/shipping", "Supply outlook"]}}, {"id": "2070145728530231537", "url": "https://x.com/aralyxMI/status/2070145728530231537", "text": "🇮🇷 The IRGC issues a warning to vessels transiting the Strait of Hormuz via undesignated routes and without permission\n\n\"Vessels transiting outside of the designated routes are responsible for any consequences\"\n\nh/t @_MartinKelly_ \n\n#oott https://t.co/Im2CBgOgDZ", "time": "14:02", "author": "aralyxMI", "author_name": "Aralyx Market Intelligence", "followers": 34, "views": 609, "likes": 1, "replies": 1, "retweets": 1, "quotes": 2, "bookmarks": 0, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bullish", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["Geopolitics", "Iran"]}}, {"id": "2070151120706765054", "url": "https://x.com/PrognosticApex/status/2070151120706765054", "text": "Oil\n#oott\n\nPlease tell me you did not sell at the apex of this falling wedge with these bullish divergences in place!? https://t.co/a3StNmf8cj", "time": "14:24", "author": "PrognosticApex", "author_name": "ApexPrognosticator", "followers": 1012, "views": 5317, "likes": 44, "replies": 3, "retweets": 3, "quotes": 2, "bookmarks": 7, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bullish", "emotional_sentiment": "Positive", "topics": ["Prices/technicals"]}}, {"id": "2070175193348165659", "url": "https://x.com/SpartaCommo/status/2070175193348165659", "text": "Japan and Korea are running refineries hard. China's independents are offline. It comes down to margins. Until they turn, don't expect Chinese runs to come back, even with cheap Iranian crude on offer.\n\nWatch the full episode here: https://t.co/TGDmW7VFWF\n\n#oott #crude #refining #oilmarkets", "time": "16:00", "author": "SpartaCommo", "author_name": "Sparta", "followers": 6127, "views": 14580, "likes": 17, "replies": 1, "retweets": 0, "quotes": 2, "bookmarks": 6, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Neutral", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["China demand", "Refining/products"]}}, {"id": "2070186310267019357", "url": "https://x.com/JavierBlas/status/2070186310267019357", "text": "Beijing’s oil import strike continues: \n\nChinese companies sold West Africa crude on Thursday, with several Nigerian and Angolan grades hitting the widest discount in at least ~15 years to the Dated Brent benchmark. \n\nIf China doesn’t show up very, very soon (or Iran doesn’t up its Hormuz games), it", "time": "16:44", "author": "JavierBlas", "author_name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "views": 235561, "likes": 789, "replies": 59, "retweets": 96, "quotes": 24, "bookmarks": 175, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bearish", "emotional_sentiment": "Negative", "topics": ["China demand", "Demand outlook"]}}, {"id": "2070186992827060731", "url": "https://x.com/NuggetCapital/status/2070186992827060731", "text": "BLAS: it’s going to get ugly in the physical oil market \n\n#oott", "time": "16:46", "author": "NuggetCapital", "author_name": "Nugget Capital Partners (NCP)", "followers": 7677, "views": 7822, "likes": 20, "replies": 10, "retweets": 0, "quotes": 0, "bookmarks": 3, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bullish", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["Supply outlook", "China demand"]}}, {"id": "2070207982432833843", "url": "https://x.com/JavierBlas/status/2070207982432833843", "text": "IMO pauses ship evacuation plan from inside the Strait of Hormuz after an attack of a vessel near the coast of Oman https://t.co/HZBsZ5WsLq", "time": "18:10", "author": "JavierBlas", "author_name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "views": 28086, "likes": 89, "replies": 4, "retweets": 18, "quotes": 2, "bookmarks": 14, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bullish", "emotional_sentiment": "Negative", "topics": ["Tankers/shipping", "Geopolitics", "Iran"]}}, {"id": "2070254140106698913", "url": "https://x.com/pickeringenergy/status/2070254140106698913", "text": "Iran Video Series #15 - crude worse than expected, bear narrative overdone, sentiment beating fundamentals (but no guarantee that changes). Watching Hormuz traffic, inventory draws, production restart, China demand restart. It ain’t dull!! #EFT #OOTT\n\nhttps://t.co/HgbCIFIOFr", "time": "21:13", "author": "pickeringenergy", "author_name": "Dan Pickering", 